<subSubSection id="24F8CDACFFB8E46B06CDECDEFBB3EE83" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6C5D9E27FFB8E46B06CDECDEFBB3EE83" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="5E964235FFB8E46B06CDECDEFEDFEEDE" bold="true" box="[199,326,1412,1437]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named for Eugenio H. Nearns (
<collectionCode id="0AF306E2FFB8E46B04B4ECDEFC95EEDF" box="[702,780,1412,1436]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/e3b9-k2i3" name="United States Department of Agriculture" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">USDA</collectionCode>
<collectionCode id="0AF306E2FFB8E46B051EECDEFCF1EEDF" box="[788,872,1412,1436]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">APHIS</collectionCode>
, Smithsonian Institution, 
<collectingRegion id="AE2650C5FFB8E46B0280ECDEFA8BEEDE" box="[1162,1298,1412,1437]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Washington</collectingRegion>
, DC, 
<collectingCountry id="14F5DEB7FFB8E46B035EECDEFA09EEDF" box="[1364,1424,1412,1436]" name="United States of America" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">USA</collectingCountry>
), for his friendship and many contributions to our knowledge of the 
<taxonomicName id="ABE2E5A4FFB8E46B058BECFDFBBFEE83" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[897,1062,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cerambycidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24F8CDACFFB8E46B06CDEC96FE00ED36" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C5D9E27FFB8E46B06CDEC96FE00ED36" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="5E964235FFB8E46B06CDEC96FEADEEA6" bold="true" box="[199,308,1484,1509]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="ABE2E5A4FFB8E46B0748EC97FE6AEEA7" authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Galileo &amp; Mcclarin, 2018" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Galileo &amp; Mcclarin" authorityYear="2018" box="[322,499,1485,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Piriana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearnsi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5E964235FFB8E46B0748EC97FE6AEEA7" box="[322,499,1485,1508]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Piriana nearnsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="45A5FF4EFFB8E46B07F0EC96FDCAEEA7" box="[506,595,1484,1509]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5E964235FFB8E46B07F0EC96FDD5EEA6" bold="true" box="[506,588,1484,1509]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="ABE2E5A4FFB8E46B04ECEC97FCACEEA7" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Galileo &amp; Mcclarin" authorityYear="2018" box="[742,821,1484,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Piriana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birai">
<emphasis id="5E964235FFB8E46B04ECEC97FCACEEA7" box="[742,821,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. birai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by: antennomere III distinctly shorter than IV; elytra with elongate yellowish brown macula basally and centrally between humerus and scutellum; elytra with 3 dorsal carina, two innermost more distinct. In 
<taxonomicName id="ABE2E5A4FFB8E46B04CFEF4FFC8FED6F" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Galileo &amp; Mcclarin" authorityYear="2018" box="[709,790,1556,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Piriana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birai">
<emphasis id="5E964235FFB8E46B04CFEF4FFC8FED6F" box="[709,790,1556,1580]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. birai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, antennomere III is about as long as IV, lighter colored elongate basal band of elytra includes humerus and extends further distally, and elytra with 2 dorsal carina, innermost less distinct.
</paragraph>
